I mean no offense to anyone or anything I have ever been a part of, but I must say…this is the finest bunch of humans I have ever had the pleasure of surrounding myself with. This community, the people, what it stands for, all of it. Every now and again I find myself as one of the organizers of this type of thing, and the fact that this group of people (and many more not pictured) find one of my events worthwhile enough to show up to is amazing to me. 

For those that came this weekend or supported it from afar, this was truly the merriest band of Scofflaws these eyes have seen. There was plenty of reason for disappointment and for celebration, but everyone had amazing attitudes.  Records were broken, curses were lifted and fun was had. Seeing the community that has continued to grow, the lifelong friendships created through it, it’s the most humbling thing I’ve ever been a part of it. If you’ve never done it, you’ll truly never understand…but wow. Thank you. 

The Southern Classic founder- Taylor

What a weekend. 

@hrslides @andrew_rodgers5 and I pulled out of the #redballgarage in Manhattan, NY and a short time later pulled into the Portifino Hotel in Redondo Beach California. Our time: 31:36, we were the first to finish. Some of you already know the significance of that time, but for those that don’t, it was a new event record for what most know as the Cannonball Run. It didn’t stand long, as just an hour later it was broken. 

That part didn’t matter, we held the record…If only for a moment. 

The biggest part of all this was the event itself. With the blessing of his family I resurrected the infamous US Express. This was the event that succeeded the Cannonball when Brock Yates was done hosting. After, Rick Doherty stepped up to put an event together for those that had unfinished business in 1980 called the Us Express. It was last ran in 1983, so nearly 40 years exactly 20 teams brought it roaring back to life. There are so many people who made it possible. To those, to the competitors, to those supporting them, and to those who came before us to pave the way, thank you.
Family. #theusexpress
